TWO men suspected to be behind a wave of hijackings in Gauteng have died. They were critically shot, while two of their partners were injured after a shootout with cops in Centurion, Tshwane this morning. Two cops were also shot and airlifted to hospital. The Gauteng specific crime trio team had been following and keeping close observation on the suspects when they were spotted in Centurion driving a black BMW 135i. As cops stopped the suspectsâ€™ car, they allegedly started firing shots at the police, who then returned fire. The two suspects were killed, while the other two were taken to hospital under police guard. 